@page "/about"

<div class="about-page">
    <div class="about-container">

        <!-- Consistent Page Hero -->
        <section class="page-hero fade-in delay-0">
            <p class="page-eyebrow">About</p>

            <h1>Background and Approach</h1>

            <p class="page-intro">
                A more personal look at how I think, what I build, and the approach behind my work.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Personal Intro -->
        <section class="about-section about-intro fade-in delay-1">
            <div class="about-intro-grid">
                <div class="about-intro-copy">
                    <div class="section-heading">
                        <p class="section-label about-label">Introduction</p>
                        <h2>I love taking ideas and turning them into something real.</h2>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        For me, development is the process. It always starts with an idea, and turning that into something real that actually works for someone is exciting and fulfilling.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        I think things like web apps should be accessible to anyone who needs them. A lot of people have something they want to build but don’t have the time or technical background to figure out how to get there and that’s where I fit in.
                        I enjoy taking someone’s idea, building it, and turning it into something they can actually use and grow with.
                        That includes how it’s designed, built, and put into use in the real world.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        My best projects are the ones that find a balance between design and function. Apps that are clean, easy to navigate, practical to use, and built in a way that makes sense long term.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="about-intro-image-wrap">
                    <img src="images/your-photo.jpg" alt="Portrait of David Padilla" class="about-intro-image" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Development Approach -->
        <section class="about-section about-build fade-in delay-2">
            <div class="section-heading">
                <p class="section-label">Development Approach</p>
                <h2>How I Build</h2>
            </div>

            <ul class="about-build-list">
                <li>Real applications over isolated demos</li>
                <li>UI designed for structure, clarity, and usability</li>
                <li>Frontends connected to APIs, services, and persistent data</li>
                <li>Clean, maintainable code with component-based architecture</li>
                <li>Projects tested and deployed in live Azure environments</li>
                <li>Iteration guided by real usage, not just first implementation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Background -->
        <section class="about-section about-background fade-in delay-3">
            <div class="background-grid">
                <div class="background-copy">
                    <div class="section-heading">
                        <p class="section-label background-label">Background</p>
                        <h2>What Shaped My Approach</h2>
                    </div>

                    <p>
                        My background in IT, operations, and Army service shaped the way I approach problems. 
                        Stay calm, look at the system, and figure out what actually needs to work.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        That mindset carried naturally into software development. 
                        Building applications from the ground up became a way to combine structure, usability, 
                        and problem-solving in a way that feels both practical and creative.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        I’ve always been drawn to hands-on problem solving, whether that’s working on something out on the water, 
                        fixing something that isn’t quite right, or building something from scratch. 
                        That same mindset carries into how I approach development. I figure it out, improve it, and make it work the way it should.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        A lot of what I know has come from building things, learning as I go, and working through problems with research, troubleshooting, 
                        and documentation to find the best possible outcome.
                    </p>

                </div>

                <div class="background-image-wrap">
                    <img src="images/your-second-photo.jpg" alt="David Padilla outdoors" class="background-image" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <PageCta Center="true"
                 Title="Let’s Work Together"
                 Message="Interested in collaborating or learning more?"
                 PrimaryText="View Resume"
                 PrimaryHref="/resume"
                 SecondaryText="Contact Me"
                 SecondaryHref="/contact" />

    </div>
</div>